I am Anirban Mitra, a Ph.D scholar advised by Dr. Manu K. Gupta at Department of Management Studies, IIT Roorkee.
My research interests are broadly related to Game Theoretical approaches to solve Business and Industrial problems such as problems in Supply chain Management, Inventory planning, Market strategy, Queueing systems etc.
I have keen interests on Machine Learning, specially in Reinforcement Learning Algorithms such as Multi Arm Bandit Problems and their Business Applications.
Apart from these I am also interested in optimization Techniques and their application in Transportation Networks and Production Planning.
On these pages I will be sharing with you my research interests, publications and academic involvements.
